results.name: a(n) = A007949(A265399(n)).
comment: a(n) = Coefficient of x in the reduction under x^2->x+1 of the polynomial encoded in the prime factorization of n. (Assuming here only polynomials with nonnegative integer coefficients, see e.g. A206296 for the details).
Completely additive with a(prime(k)) = F(k-1), where F(k) denotes the k-th Fibonacci number, A000045(k). - _Peter Munn_, Mar 29 2021, incorporating comment by _Antti Karttunen_, Dec 15 2015
link: Antti Karttunen, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..100
